      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Beginning May all Great Northern\npassenger trains will stop at all sta\ntions along the line between Spokane\nand Seattle, according to the arrange\nments made by F. l. Whitney after\nhe left this city last week.\n\n\nIn company with S. G. Yerkes he\nwent over the line carefully and came\nto the conclusion that by having all\ntrains stop at all the stations it would\nbe of great benefit to the smaller\ntowns along the line. At present the\none or the other of the through trains\nbetween Spokane and Seattle only\nmakes occasional stops and in many\ncases the inhabitants of small towns"
    }
